FBIS3-41113 "jptdd005__l94050" JPRS-TDD-94-005-L Document Type:JPRS Document Title:Narcotics 1 February 1994 NEAR EAST & SOUTH ASIA PAKISTAN Poppy Crops Destroyed in Bajaur BK3101163894 Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network in Urdu 1500 GMT 31 Jan 94 BK3101163894 Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network Language: Urdu Article Type:BFN [Text] A high-level meeting in Peshawar was informed today that poppy crops covering 2,090 kanals [approximately 289 acres] of land were destroyed in Bajaur Agency during the current season. Acting Governor Major General, retired, Khurshid Ali Khan, who chaired the meeting, directed that the law enforcement agencies make all-out efforts to eliminate poppy cultivation and heroin laboratories.
